#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:1
msgid "Using _Black_ with Jupyter Notebooks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:3
msgid ""
"_Black_ supports formatting Jupyter Notebooks (`.ipynb` files) natively."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:5
msgid "Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:7
msgid "To format Jupyter Notebooks, install _Black_ with the `jupyter` extra:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:9
msgid "pip install \"black[jupyter]\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:14
msgid ""
"Without the `jupyter` extra, _Black_ will not be able to format `.ipynb` "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:17
msgid "Basic usage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:19
msgid ""
"Once installed, you can format notebooks the same way you format Python "
"files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:21
msgid "black notebook.ipynb\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:25
msgid ""
"You can also format entire directories containing a mix of `.py` and `."
"ipynb` files:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:27
msgid "black .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:31
msgid ""
"_Black_ will automatically detect Jupyter Notebooks by their `.ipynb` "
"extension and format them accordingly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:34
msgid "Formatting via standard input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:36
msgid ""
"If you're piping notebook content on standard input, use the `--ipynb` flag "
"to tell _Black_ to treat the input as a Jupyter Notebook:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:39
msgid "cat notebook.ipynb | black --ipynb -\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:43
msgid "What is (and isn't) formatted"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:45
msgid ""
"_Black_ formats the Python code cells in your notebook while preserving:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:47
msgid "Markdown cells"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:48
msgid "Cell outputs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:49
msgid "Cell metadata"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:50
msgid "Notebook metadata"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:52
msgid "Only the source code within Python code cells is reformatted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:54
msgid "Cells that _Black_ will skip"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:56
msgid ""
"_Black_ is cautious about formatting notebook cells. The following cells "
"will **not** be formatted:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:59
msgid "**Automagics** — e.g. `pip install black` (without the `%` prefix)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:60
msgid "**Non-Python cell magics** — e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:61
msgid ""
"%%writefile script.py\n"
"print(\"hello\")\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:65
msgid "**Multiline magics** — e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:66
msgid ""
"%timeit f(1, \\\n"
"        2, \\\n"
"        3)\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:71
msgid ""
"**IPython internal calls** — code that `IPython`'s `TransformerManager` "
"would transform, e.g.:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:73
msgid "get_ipython().system('ls')\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:76
msgid ""
"**Invalid syntax** — as it cannot be safely distinguished from automagics "
"without a running IPython kernel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:79
msgid ""
"If you notice a cell is not being formatted, it is likely because it "
"contains one of the above constructs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:82
msgid ""
"Additionally, _Black_ cannot format Jupyter Notebooks with the `--line-"
"ranges` option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:84
msgid "Cell magics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:86
msgid ""
"_Black_ understands IPython magics, but is conservative about which cells it "
"will format. By default, _Black_ recognizes standard IPython magics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:89
msgid "Custom python cell magics"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:91
msgid ""
"If you use custom cell magics that contain Python code, you can tell _Black_ "
"about them using the `--python-cell-magics` flag:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:94
msgid "black --python-cell-magics writefile notebook.ipynb\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:98
msgid "This also works in `pyproject.toml`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:100
msgid ""
"[tool.black]\n"
"python-cell-magics = [\"writefile\", \"my_custom_magic\"]\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:105
msgid "Integrations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:107
msgid "pre-commit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:109
msgid "Simply replace the `black` hook with `black-jupyter`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:111
msgid ""
"repos:\n"
"  - repo: https://github.com/psf/black-pre-commit-mirror\n"
"    rev: 26.5.1\n"
"    hooks:\n"
"      - id: black-jupyter\n"
"        language_version: python3.11\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:120
msgid ""
"See the [source version control integration](../integrations/"
"source_version_control.md) docs for more examples of using Black with pre-"
"commit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:123
msgid "GitHub Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:125
msgid "Set the `jupyter` option to `true`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:127
msgid ""
"- uses: psf/black@stable\n"
"  with:\n"
"    jupyter: true\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../guides/using_black_with_jupyter_notebooks.md:133
msgid ""
"See the [GitHub Actions integration](../integrations/source_version_control."
"md) docs for more examples of using Black with GitHub Actions."
msgstr ""
